Introduction

Luda is a South Korean singer and actress, best known as a member of the girl group WJSN (Cosmic Girls) representing Pisces zodiac sign, its sub-unit WJSN CHOCOME, and the project girl group WJMK. She initially trained under SM Entertainment before joining Starship Entertainment and making her debut with WJSN on February 25, 2016, as a sub-vocalist for their first mini-album Would You Like?

In 2018, Luda joined the special collaboration unit WJMK, a four-member group formed by Starship Entertainment and Fantagio. The unit, which also included Weki Meki members Yoojung and Doyeon, released the single "Strong" in June 2018. Later, in 2020, Luda became part of the sub-unit WJSN CHOCOME alongside members Dayoung, Soobin, and Yeoreum. Their debut single album Hmph! was released on October 7, 2020, with the title track of the same name.

In addition to her musical career, Luda made her acting debut in 2022 with the web drama My X Twenty, marking a new chapter in her entertainment career. On March 3, 2023, it was confirmed that Luda would not renew her contract with Starship Entertainment, though she remained a member of WJSN. Shortly after, she signed with iHQ on April 19, 2023, to focus on her acting endeavors. Luda eventually debuted as Keuang in the virtual project group FE:VERSE on May 9, 2023.
